1. 12. tribuni aerarii] These consisted of respectable and well-to- do people of the plebs, in earlier times charged with the raising of the war-tax (tributum) and the distribution of pay to the army. By the lex Aurelia B. C. 70 they formed a distinct ordo and shared the iudicia with the senators and equites. This judicial office was taken from them by Julius Caesar, Sueton. Caes. c. 41 iudicia ad cluo genera iudicum redegit, equestris ordinis ac senatorii ‚⁶ tribu nos aerarios, quoderat tertium, sustulit.
